$ Python - getpass
@ getpass

`getpass` provides two functions:
  • `getpass()` to read a value without echoing it, typically used to enter → development/security/password[passwords] (see → development/languages/Python/built-in/functions/input#py-input-password[here])
  • `getuser()` returns the login name for the currenlty logged in user

